arXiv:2606.08273v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: The recent Belle II measurement of $\mathcal{B}(B^+	o K^+
u ar{
u})$, which deviates from the Standard Model prediction, provides a strong motivation to search for New Physics in $b	o s
u ar{
u}$ transitions. We perform a model-independent analysis within the low-energy effective theory, focusing on dimension-six vector operators involving right-handed neutrinos. Using the Belle II measurement of $\mathcal{B}({B	o K
u ar{
u}})$ together with the upper limit on $\mathcal{B}({B	o K^{*}
u ar{
u}})$, we constrain the new physics interactions. We study the correlation of $\mathcal{B}({B	o K
u ar{
u}})$ with $\mathcal{B}({B	o K^{*}
u ar{
u}})$, $\mathcal{B}({B_s	o\phi
u ar{
u}})$, $\mathcal{B}({\Lambda_b	o\Lambda
u ar{
u}})$, and the longitudinal polarization fraction $F_L^{K^*}$. We find sizeable enhancements in all branching fractions studied, while $F_L^{K^*}$ offers complementary sensitivity to the underlying RHN interaction structure. These results provide testable signatures of right-handed neutrino interactions at Belle~II and LHCb, and at the future FCC-ee experiment.
